From: Chenhui Zhao <chenhui.zhao@freescale.com>
Date: Fri, 14 Mar 2014 17:19:57 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 10/57] powerpc/t104x: enable wakeup sources(Add DTS missing
 parts)

Set the register IPPDEXPCR (IP Powerdown Exception Control Register) to
enable IP blocks which work as wakeup source when sleep/deep sleep.

Change-Id: Id95cb920cab90e12851995d039bd866e6388f8ae
Signed-off-by: Chenhui Zhao <chenhui.zhao@freescale.com>
Reviewed-on: http://git.am.freescale.net:8181/10711
Tested-by: Review Code-CDREVIEW <CDREVIEW@freescale.com>
Reviewed-by: Yang Li <LeoLi@freescale.com>
Reviewed-by: Jose Rivera <German.Rivera@freescale.com>

[Original patch taken from QorIQ-SDK-V1.8-20150619-yocto.
 WRL8 ported a similar patch before, but I removed it in patch

"ppc: DTS: remove all t104* DTS files."

to align with SDK, readd it now. Just port the DTS changes.
Ignore the changes of "arch/powerpc/platforms/85xx/qoriq_pm.c"
since it has been updated in previous patch.]
Signed-off-by: Yanjiang Jin <yanjiang.jin@windriver.com>
